<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-60-0621 </DOCNO><TEXT>This volume has detailed some of the major techniques available in thepractice of oncology. The author puts these in the perspective of cancerincidence, prevention, diagnosis and treatment. Theoretically, the effectsof cancer can be counteracted by prevention; early diagnosis; treatment;rehabilitation; and, perhaps most important of all, by research whichincreases our knowledge in all these fields. These topics are consideredin turn.</TEXT></DOC>